<section id="volmeslide-content-home" class="volume-slide-step">
  <div class="container text-center is-light-grey py-5">
    <nav
      class="[ volume-slide-step__navigation ] [ navbar navbar-expand-sm navbar-dark ps-4 ]"
    >
      <span class="navbar-brand mb-0"> Volume Slide Step </span>
      <div class="navbar-nav">
        <a href="#content-about" class="nav-link mx-2">
          About
        </a>
        <a href="#content-help" class="nav-link mx-2">
          Help
        </a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="row py-5 justify-content-around">
      <div
        class="[ volume-slide-step__song-speed ] [ col-10 col-md-5 pt-3 pb-4 rounded mb-5 ]"
      >
        <h4 class="mb-2"> Song speed </h4>
        <div>
          <input
            type="number"
            id="tics-input"
            value="6"
            min="1"
            max="31"
            title="Song speed ranges from 1 to 31"
            class="rounded text-center group-change"
          />
          <span> tic(s) per row </span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="[ volume-slide-step__instrument-volume ] [ col-10 col-md-5 pt-3 pb-4 rounded mb-5 ]"
      >
        <h4 class="mb-2"> Instrument Volume </h4>
        <div>
          <input
            type="number"
            id="instrument-volume-input"
            value="64"
            min="1"
            max="64"
            title="Instrument volume ranges from 1 to 64"
            class="rounded text-center group-change"
          />
          <span> volume level </span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="[ volume-slide-step__volume-slide ] [ col-10 col-md-5 pt-3 pb-4 rounded mb-5 ]"
      >
        <h4 class="mb-2"> Volume Slide </h4>
        <div>
          <input
            type="number"
            id="units-input"
            value="1"
            min="1"
            max="15"
            title="Number units of units per command ranges from 1 to 15"
            class="rounded text-center group-change"
          />
          <span> unit(s) per command </span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="w-100"></div>
      <div
        class="[ volume-slide-step__result ] [ col-10 col-md-5 pt-3 pb-4 rounded mb-5 ]"
      >
        <h4 class="mb-2"> Volume Slide </h4>
        <div id="commands-result-container">
          <span
            id="commands-result"
            title="Number of commands ranges from 1 to 64"
            class="volume-slide-step__result__number-of-commands h5"
          >
            0
          </span>
          <span> command(s) per row </span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="fineslide-checkbox"> Fine Volume Slide </label>
          <input
            type="checkbox"
            id="fineslide-checkbox"
            class="volume-slide-step__result__fineslide"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        id="fineslide-container"
        class="[ volume-slide-step__result ] [col-10 col-md-5 pt-3 pb-4 d-none rounded mb-5 ]"
      >
        <h4 class="mb-2"> Fine Volume Slide </h4>
        <div id="units-result-container">
          <span
            id="units-result"
            title="Number of units ranges from hex 1 to f"
            class="volume-slide-step__result__units-per-command h5"
          >
            0
          </span>
          <span> unit(s) per command </span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="w-100"></div>
      <div class="col-10 col-md-5 py-2 mb-5 rounded justify-content-center">
        <div class="row justify-content-around">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="reset-button"
            title="Reset to default values"
            class="btn btn-primary w-25"
          >
            Reset
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="content-about" class="volume-slide-step__about">
  <article class="container pt-5 pb-5">
    <header class="volume-slide-step__about__header">
      <h2 class="pt-5">
        About... Volume Slide Step
      </h2>
    </header>
    <div class="w-75 py-3">
      <p class="text-justify">
        The tool
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide Step
        </span>
        is used in conjunction with the music editor
        <span class="fw-bold">
          <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ProTracker"
            class="volume-slide-step__about__link"
          >
            ProTracker.
          </a>
        </span>
        This tracker uses the effect commands
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide / Fine Volume Slide
        </span>
        which do a linear slide up or down.
      </p>
      <p>
        The only difference between them is at which ticks they are executed.
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Fine Volume Slide
        </span>
        is executed every first tic whereas
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide
        </span>
        the rest of the tics, song_speed-1 times.
      </p>
      <p>
        The arguments for these commands are called
        <span class="fw-bold">
          number of units
        </span>
        and are given as hex numbers. This value is added to or substracted of
        the current instrument volume value.
      </p>
      <p>
        To get the right number of commands for
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide
        </span>
        and the units for
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Fine Volume Slide
        </span>
        for a complete slide up or down, this tool is a very comfortable aid.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>

<section id="content-help" class="volume-slide-step__help">
  <article class="container pt-5 pb-5">
    <header class="volume-slide-step__help__header">
      <h2 class="pt-5"> Help </h2>
    </header>
    <div class="w-75 py-3">
      <p class="text-justify">
        This tool works with two output results:
      </p>
      <p>
        1. One output for the case that only the command
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide
        </span>
        is used.
      </p>
      <p>
        2. If the volume slide should be more precise, then
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Fine Volume Slide
        </span>
        can be enabled by the checkbox.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can toggle between these two modes by setting or unsetting the
        checkbox.
      </p>
      <p>
        The units of the command
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Fine Volume Slide
        </span>
        are used for the remainder of the division to calculate the
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide
        </span>
        commands per row.
      </p>
      <p>
        The fine slide units are only for one
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Fine Volume Slide
        </span>
        command. If fine slide values are disabled, then the number of
        <span class="fw-bold">
          Volume Slide
        </span>
        commands is rounded upwards to the nearest integer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>

